# Git Commit Conventions

## Strip the Cursor coauthor trailer

When `CURSOR_AGENT=1` (set by default inside Cursor's agent runtime), every
`git commit` gets a `Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>` trailer
appended. This trailer is NOT wanted on this repo.

`--no-verify` does NOT bypass it — the trailer is added by Cursor's git
wrapper, not a hook. The reliable fix is to unset the env var per-command.

### Rule

Always prefix `git commit` with `env -u CURSOR_AGENT`:

❌ BAD
```bash
git commit -m "fix: something"
git commit --no-verify -m "fix: something"
```

✅ GOOD
```bash
env -u CURSOR_AGENT git commit -m "fix: something"
env -u CURSOR_AGENT git commit --amend -m "fix: something"
```

Verify the result with `git log -1 --format=fuller` — there must be no
`Co-authored-by:` line.

## Message style

- Single-line subject. No body unless the user explicitly asks for one.
- Conventional Commits prefix: `feat:`, `fix:`, `chore:`, `docs:`,
  `refactor:`, `test:`, with optional scope (e.g. `chore(scaffold): …`).
- Match the existing repo style — check `git log --oneline -10` before
  drafting.

## Author

Author and committer must always be `danisharora099 <danisharora099@gmail.com>`.
Never add any `Co-authored-by` trailer (Cursor, Claude, Composer, or otherwise).
